     A Label placeholder should be filled in with an integer constant that
has no more than four digits.  Labels that appear in the instruction part
of a program or subprogram should be declared in the LABEL declaration sec-
tion of that program or subprogram.
     Labels may be used to label statements or in a GOTO instruction.
